title: Drawing, Design for Six-Legged Round Dining Table, 1900–05
title_raw: Design for Six-Legged Round Dining Table
medium: Pen and black in , graphite on thin cream paper
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite, upper center of image: Round Dining Table / 5'. 0" Diam - 12," 0" Ext-; at lower right if image with arrow pointing to foot above caster: Brass Boots-; along bottom of sheet, center: [illeg.] Oak or Mah'g Extension Table; at lower right corner of sheet: No 9
creditline: Gift of The Lake St. Louis Historical Society
description: Round table top with dividing stretcher running across center, raised on 6 plain, straight, tapering legs on cup casters; legs clustered in pairs, one pair at either end and one pair center.

participants.person_name: The Lake St. Louis Historical Society
